FAQs
What are the eligibility criteria for studying at the University of Nicosia?

Applicants must have completed their secondary education and meet the specific requirements of their chosen program. Proficiency in English is also required, as most programs are taught in English.

How much does it cost to study at the University of Nicosia?

Tuition fees vary by program and level of study, averaging between €9,000 to €15,000 per year. Living expenses typically range from €600 to €1,000 per month.

Are there scholarships available for international students?

Yes, the University of Nicosia offers various scholarships based on academic merit, financial need, and specific talents. Additionally, the Cypriot government and private organizations provide scholarship opportunities.

What is the application process for the University of Nicosia?

The application process involves submitting an online application through the university’s portal, along with academic transcripts, a personal statement, letters of recommendation, and proof of English proficiency.

Can international students work while studying in Cyprus?

Yes, international students in Cyprus are allowed to work part-time during their studies and full-time during holidays, providing an opportunity to gain work experience and support their living expenses.
